<div class="section" id="about">
<h2>About the Mission</h2>
<p>
Chandrayaan-3 is India's third lunar mission launched by the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO).
The mission successfully landed on the Moon on 23 August 2023, making India the fourth country in
the world to achieve a soft landing on the lunar surface.
</p>
</div>
<div class="section" id="achievement">
<h2>Historic Achievements</h2>
<ul>
<li>First country to land near the Moon’s south pole.</li>
<li>India became the 4th nation to achieve a soft landing on the Moon.</li>
<li>The Vikram lander and Pragyan rover conducted experiments on the lunar surface.</li>
<li>Showcased India's growing strength in space technology.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="section" id="tribute">
<h2>Tribute</h2>
<p>
This mission is a tribute to the dedication, intelligence, and hard work of Indian scientists.
Chandrayaan-3 inspired millions of students and proved that with determination and innovation,
India can achieve extraordinary milestones in space exploration.
</p>
